2009-10-23  Paul Hilfinger  <hilfingr@tully.CS.Berkeley.EDU>

	* Version 4.6.9.
	
	* share/lib/TestingCommon.pl (UnpackSubmission, UnpackDirectSubmission):
	Refactor and always add .SUBMISSION file regardless of the kind of
	submission (direct or SVN).

2009-10-21  Paul Hilfinger  <hilfingr@tully.CS.Berkeley.EDU>

	* Version 4.6.8.
	
	* share/lib/GradingCommon.pl: Initialize SUBMISSION_DIR without the
	setgid bit.  Otherwise, when staff accounts other than cs61b 
	create new assignment directories, these directories get the
	staff group, but are not owned by the class master, making
	them inaccessible to glookup -t, even though it is setuid class
	master (this is because setuid root does NOT update the 
	supplemental group list of the process).  
	* share/bin/suid/copy-submission: Just use 0777 as protection on
	new assignment directories, which are already protected by the 
	parent directory's access.  Redundant, but consistent with change to
	GradingCommon.pl, above.
	* share/bin/svn-log-submission: Ditto.

	* share/bin/bug-submit: Adjust bug-submit subject and reply-to
	address to reflect both the user login and the user's registered
	email address.
	Skip .svn directories.
	
